 ways), it's probably fine <br />too, but let's face it, who the hell knows? But it's not going to be an <br />issue for laptops and normal desktops.<br /><br />For multi-lun, I suspect the luns are related, and there might be some <br />ordering issues. But it's _likely_ all fine there too.<br /><br />The nice thing about systems with wires (ie USB, SCSI, SATA) is that it's <br />really hard to make different devices have odd dependencies on each other. <br />The wires tend to _be_ the topology.<br /><br />			Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
